This paper uses graph grammars and rule composition to model chemical reactions, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The application of these techniques to chemistry falls under the category of computational chemistry (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the use of graph grammars for summarizing complex reactions, which is related to graph summarization (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the study of natural compounds, which could potentially fall under deep learning (cs.DL) if neural networks are used to analyze the data.
